down the gurgler
Homonym Number:
Word Class:phrase
Sense Number:
Definition:washed away, beaten, ruined
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: OED online: A person or thing that gurgles; spec. in <b>Austral. slang</b>, a plughole, drain; freq. in fig. phrases down the gurgler, etc. (cf. DRAIN n. 1 e).
